dataIdInfo.idPurp: Data is to be used as a reference for watershed subbasins for the City of Bothell. Please read description to help guide you for specifc data usage.
dataIdInfo.idAbs:
Individual subbasins were identified using general watershed characteristics. A basin typically had a stream with a single confluence, catchment, to either North Creek, or Sammamish River. There are some minor exceptions in instances when storm water structures may traverse watershed boundaries or fall in between watershed boundaries with their own piped discharge to North Creek or the Sammamish River. Starting at the confluence and working up stream direction contours and storm water layers were used to delineate watershed basin boundaries. There are undoubtably errors over the precise watershed basin boundaries. We did not conduct any field verification. In some cases we used anecdotal information, but the majority of boundaries relied on contours and storm water infrastructure as the means to determine watershed basin boundaries.

Subbasin boundaries were modified where they did not follow elevation changes of the landscape and where boundaries intersected or did not contain storm water facilities, structures, and pipes. These edits are based on visual inspection, in ArcMap and on enlarged hard-copy maps, of the...
